<section class="relative clear  ">

        <div class="panel panel--tabbed-icons panel--full-width" id="20b934a6-9d73-ec11-94f6-281878925e61">
            <div class="panel__inner">
                    <h2 class="panel__heading">How to apply</h2>
                                    <div class="fp-list-tabbed" role="tablist" id="tablist-20b934a6-9d73-ec11-94f6-281878925e61">
                        <div class="fp-list-tabbed__tabs">

                                <button class="tab-1 fp-list-tabbed__tab active"
                                        role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="panel-90768810-8c46-4aad-b0b1-12cd2a6dd192" id="tab-90768810-8c46-4aad-b0b1-12cd2a6dd192"  data-tablist="tablist-20b934a6-9d73-ec11-94f6-281878925e61">

                                    <span class="fp-list-tabbed-tab__text">Firm up your offer</span>
                                </button>
                                <button class="tab-2 fp-list-tabbed__tab "
                                        role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="panel-1b2bc652-d494-493f-9ce0-cb57b561263e" id="tab-1b2bc652-d494-493f-9ce0-cb57b561263e" tabindex="-1" data-tablist="tablist-20b934a6-9d73-ec11-94f6-281878925e61">

                                    <span class="fp-list-tabbed-tab__text">Choose your halls</span>
                                </button>
                                <button class="tab-3 fp-list-tabbed__tab "
                                        role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="panel-7a20386b-b9e4-44aa-be81-d983e15cb5fd" id="tab-7a20386b-b9e4-44aa-be81-d983e15cb5fd" tabindex="-1" data-tablist="tablist-20b934a6-9d73-ec11-94f6-281878925e61">

                                    <span class="fp-list-tabbed-tab__text">Apply</span>
                                </button>
                                <button class="tab-4 fp-list-tabbed__tab "
                                        role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="panel-395bb2dc-8e56-4676-b5a4-df71c4e1b10e" id="tab-395bb2dc-8e56-4676-b5a4-df71c4e1b10e" tabindex="-1" data-tablist="tablist-20b934a6-9d73-ec11-94f6-281878925e61">

                                    <span class="fp-list-tabbed-tab__text">What next?</span>
                                </button>
                        </div>


                        <div class="fp-list-tabbed__panels">
                                <div id="panel-90768810-8c46-4aad-b0b1-12cd2a6dd192" class="fp-list-tabbed__panel tab-1-panel active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-90768810-8c46-4aad-b0b1-12cd2a6dd192">
                                    <h3>Firm up your offer</h3>
<p>To apply for accommodation at Birmingham City University, you first need to accept us as your firm or insurance choice. Applications for the Academic Year 2024/25 will open from 1 February 2024. After accepting your offer, please allow up to 24 hours for the system to update with your details before you register and then apply in the Accommodation Portal. All first-year, full-time home and international students are guaranteed University accommodation if they have firmly accepted an offer in the main application cycle and apply by the deadline date.</p>                                    
                                </div>
                                <div id="panel-1b2bc652-d494-493f-9ce0-cb57b561263e" class="fp-list-tabbed__panel tab-2-panel " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-1b2bc652-d494-493f-9ce0-cb57b561263e">
                                    <h3>Choose your halls</h3>
<p>When applying you will need to know which halls you would prefer to stay in. You will be asked to give preferences during the application process. </p>                                    <a class="button--primary button--small" href="/student-info/accommodation/halls" target="_self">View our accommodation</a>
                                </div>
                                <div id="panel-7a20386b-b9e4-44aa-be81-d983e15cb5fd" class="fp-list-tabbed__panel tab-3-panel " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-7a20386b-b9e4-44aa-be81-d983e15cb5fd">
                                    <h3>Apply</h3>
<p>Applications for the Academic year 2024/25 will open from 1 February 2024. After accepting your offer, please allow up to 24 hours for the system to update with your details before you register and then apply in the Accommodation Portal.</p>                                    <a class="button--primary button--small" href="https://roomservice.bcu.ac.uk/BCU_Portal/" target="_self">Apply for accommodation</a>
                                </div>
                                <div id="panel-395bb2dc-8e56-4676-b5a4-df71c4e1b10e" class="fp-list-tabbed__panel tab-4-panel " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-395bb2dc-8e56-4676-b5a4-df71c4e1b10e">
                                    <h3>What next?</h3>
<p>The allocation of rooms begins from 7 February 2024 for those students who have already accepted an unconditional course offer. When you have been allocated a room, you will receive an email informing you of the room you have been offered and at which point you must follow the instructions in that email to accept the room offered. To accept your room offer you will be required to make either a deposit or advance payment within the deadline date (three days for UK and five days for international students). For the majority of the accommodation sites you are required to provide a guarantor. Please see each of the accommodation pages or click on the Facilities Summary. All offers for Beech Gardens, Bentley House, Jennens Court, Lakeside, Queens Hospital Close, Staniforth House, The Heights, The Old Fire Station and Hamstead will be sent by email with a deadline by which you must respond to the respective site provider.</p>                                    
                                </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
            </div>
        </div>
</section>

<section class="relative clear  ">

        <div class="panel panel--vertical-stack panel--vertical-stack-nolinks panel--full-width">
            <div class="panel__inner">
                    <h2 class="panel__heading">Frequently asked questions</h2>
                <p><span>These are the FAQs for our BCU managed and partner halls of residence and the sections are listed in relevance for you.</span></p>                                    <div>
                        <ul class="panel--vertical-stack__items">
                                <li class="vertical-stack-item">
                                    <div class="vertical-stack-item__content">
                                        <p class="vertical-stack-item__title">How do I apply for accommodation?</p>
<p>You will need to know your choices of accommodation prior to making an application. If there are medical or mobility factors which have a bearing on your accommodation needs, please provide full details.</p>                                    </div>
                                </li>
                                <li class="vertical-stack-item">
                                    <div class="vertical-stack-item__content">
                                        <p class="vertical-stack-item__title">When will I know I have been allocated a room?</p>
<p>You will receive an email from Accommodation Services informing you that you have been offered a room, please ensure you accept and make the relevant payment required before the offer deadline date.</p>                                    </div>
                                </li>
                                <li class="vertical-stack-item">
                                    <div class="vertical-stack-item__content">
                                        <p class="vertical-stack-item__title">When will I be able to move in?</p>
<p>Before you can move into your accommodation, you will be asked to complete the online induction. You will receive an email with instructions on how to complete this process.</p>                                    </div>
                                </li>
                                <li class="vertical-stack-item">
                                    <div class="vertical-stack-item__content">
                                        <p class="vertical-stack-item__title">How much will the rent be per month?</p>
<p>Please see individual accommodation location pages for rent prices.</p>                                    </div>
                                </li>
                                <li class="vertical-stack-item">
                                    <div class="vertical-stack-item__content">
                                        <p class="vertical-stack-item__title">What if I don&#39;t have an Application Number?</p>
<p>Your University Application Number should be on your offer letter. It is made up of eight unique numbers. If it isn't on your offer letter, please contact Accommodation Services.</p>                                    </div>
                                </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel__ctas panel__ctas--centered">
                        <a class="button--primary" href="/student-info/accommodation/faqs" target="_self">Read all FAQs</a>
                    </div>
            </div>
        </div>
</section>    <section class="relative clear  panel-background--lgrey-1">

